<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7170> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7170" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator in 45, who, with Cn. Domitius Calvinus (43), took the oath on behalf of the Roman people in a treaty with Cnidus (A. Jarde, Mel. Cagnat [1912] 52-58; C. Cichorius, RhM 76, 1927, 327-329). Hanslik in RE would identify him with Cn. Pompeius Q. f. ? n. Rufus (112). Cos. Suff. 31, but the tribe, Collina or Velina, is inconsistent with the Clustumina or Arnensis of the Pompeii Rufi. See Wiseman (CQ 14, 1964, 125), who follows Cichorius in favoring Pomponius Rufus, perhaps brother of the monetalis (26) and son of the tr. Pl. of 90 (3).\n" .
